Manchester City are still waiting to complete the £32million signing of Porto defender Eliaquim Mangala despite footage leaking out of the player discussing his move.

It is understood that the video vault on City’s website was hacked, leading to the interview briefly appearing on the internet before being taken down.

However, it was filmed 12 days ago when Mangala travelled to Manchester for his medical and a tour of the club’s Carrington training facility before going on holiday.

